language Essence 1.3

given numItems: int(1..)
given itemSize: matrix indexed by [int(1..numItems)] of int(1..)
given binCap: int(1..)
letting maxBins be numItems
find assignment: matrix indexed by [int(1..numItems)] of int(1..maxBins)
find used: matrix indexed by [int(1..maxBins)] of int(0..1)
find numBins: int(1..maxBins)
minimising numBins
such that
    and([sum([toInt(assignment[item] = bin) * itemSize[item] | item : int(1..numItems)]) <= binCap
             | bin : int(1..maxBins)]),
    and([used[bin] = toInt(or([assignment[item] = bin | item : int(1..numItems)])) | bin : int(1..maxBins)]),
    numBins = sum([used[bin] | bin : int(1..maxBins)]),
    sum([used[bin] | bin : int(1..maxBins)]) =
    sum([toInt(or([assignment[item] = bin | item : int(1..numItems)])) | bin : int(1..maxBins)])

